entries.femaleVariant: So? We goin' in?
Sounds sensible. Better get comfy.
Let's just drop it.
Peeps on the streets hate the corps.
[Stand] I'm getting worse...
I think it is time to do something, hm?
I wish to be certain we have not overlooked anything.
We should wait and observe.
The bakeneko got sick of us, looks like.
V?
What?
Gulp. No sudden movements.
Do you see it?
The cat.
Thought they'd all disappeared from the city.
So? Just some stray.
Fine-lookin' feline. Thought they'd all disappeared from the city.
So? Cat like any other.
entries.maleVariant: So? It's a cat like any other.

entries.femaleVariant: You already forget what happened at Tom's Diner? People hate corps more'n anything.
entries.maleVariant: You already forget what happened at Tom's Diner? People hate corps more than anything.

entries.femaleVariant: Tired of bickerin'. Let's just drop it.
You got no idea how I feel.
Huh, finally starting to make some sense.
Sometimes I wish to become a nomad. To leave this world, forget everything.
Finally startin' to make some sense.
It will find its own way.
Hmph. Is this what you said before entering Konpeki Plaza?
As will we.
If nothing out of the ordinary happens, then yes – "We goin' in!"
About Jack? What is it?
When I set out to find you, others went to find Jackie. They took his body.
For the life of me, can't figure why. So his mom couldn't give him a proper sendoff?
Arasaka has a method... for pulling information from the dead.
What're you talkin' about?
Don't ask for details, I understand little. I know they use the Soulkiller program to do so.
They can pull an engram from Welles' body. Damaged, incomplete, but still an engram.
That's bullshit.
Don't believe it. Pure bullshit.
You survived your death. Is this also "bullshit?"
Where are they holding it?
Jackie's psyche – where're are they keepin' it?
This I do not know.
Slavin' away for a corp's not for everybody.
Slavin' away for a corp – not exactly everybody's dream.
Why'm I only hearin' this now?
I did not know I could trust you. The circumstances have changed.
I'm not judging you.
Never too late to change.
Do you know what I think?
That day in Konpeki, we both have lost someone important.
Don't be smart, got no idea what I feel.
Wasn't judging you.
And we are not at peace with this, so we seek conflict, argue eagerly.
There is one thing you should know... It is about Mr. Welles…
It is the duty of the living to atone for the dead.
Hanako-sama shall aid us in our mission.
Or she'll make sure we die for good.
Never too late.
Pff. Nomads aren't anythin' like that.
And you know what? Nobody owns me. I'm free. You should try it.
Nomads aren't lone wolves with egos. Whether they're blood or not – family comes first.
I sense that you judge me. And yet you have no right to.
Unlike you and your friend Mr. Welles, I was not arrogant, I did not take the easy path.
Sayin' you got no dirt on your hands?
You forgetting I worked for Arasaka?
Forgetting I was at Arasaka? Saw how corps operate – wasn't roses and rainbows.
Untrue. You oppose the corporations, their order, their world, in a mindless way, yet you offer no worthy alternative.
You show me filthy streets as if no other world exists, as if nothing else is possible. What of the millions who work for Arasaka and receive stability, safety?
And Chiba-11's slumrats? They're there, scraping scraps out of scoptins… Corps decided that, too.
Corporations need capital and resources to keep all in order. Who else is to rule? Corrupt governments? The masses – attached to feeders?
Cynics, nihilists – like you?
Sayin' you got no dirt on your hands?
There are no clean hands. But it is important how they become dirty.
So spill – how'd you sully yours?
Arasaka gave me what no one else could – values I could honor, live for. This was most important.
Believe in ghosts?
It is the first animal I see in Night City. Except cockroaches, of course.
Perhaps it is a bakeneko?
Nope, just a cat.
Who knows – could be.
Bakeneko?
A "bakeneko?" What's that?
First it was birds, then dogs – cats actually put up a fight longest.
Believe in ghosts?
Chill. Just a cat.
Feline ghost? Ah, suppose anything's possible.
It is a cat spirit – it brings misfortune, can restore the dead back to life.
The Relic lets you talk to the dead, does it not? I believe we are past belief.
Perhaps. Perhaps not.
My grandmother knew many, many stories about kitsune, kappa – bakeneko, too.
Miss home?
Where'd you grow up?
Miss home?
Where'd you grow up, anyway?
A foolish question.
I am from the slums of Chiba-11. Once, when I was desperate to leave there, I…
Egh, bad memories washed away by time. I long only for the simple days of childhood.
Remember when I was a kid…
What was it like – growin' up in Chiba-11?
Remember when I was a kid…
Remember when I was a kid…
Growin' up in Chiba-11 – what was it like?
My childhood, let's see... Nights spent lookin' for a star – any star… All dimmed by city lights.
My childhood, let's see... Racin' my bobber for the first time through the hills...
Childhood memories, let's see... Hoppin' buildings, runnin' away from badges.
Silent lullabies sung by the flickering neon signs of Charter Hill…
I remember the chemical stench of the canal where we boys washed our shirts.
Oh, and uh, first kiss in the middle of a synth-cornfield…
Iron taste of blood from a split lip…
Corporate transporters sometimes passed through our slum. Arasaka selecting children – but only the clean ones.
What'd they need kids for?
They recruit you for military service?
Military transporters? For a slum?
What'd they need kids for?
Lemme guess – so they could turn 'em into corposoldiers?
Transporters, you say.
To be corporate soldiers.
Exactly.
Armored and armed. Chiba-11 had the most murders in all Japan. It probably still has.
When they chose me, I felt I had won the lottery.
In the army I was given everything I lacked before – discipline, regular meals, and when I proved I was gifted – an education.
All you had to do was kill Arasaka's enemies.
Anything's good that puts food on the table.
And all you had to do in return was kill Saburo's enemies.
Did what you had to to keep from goin' hungry.
You dirty your hands for money. I, in the name of principles.
Take a look around. It's here – your corporate world in its glorious splendor.
C'mon, not everybody wants to change the world.
Sadly, this is true.
We cannot fix everything at once.
Can't blame 'em, either. Got some regrets, but kleppin' from Arasaka ain't one of 'em.
What's that?
Motherfuckers… evil.
How'd you come to be Saburo's bodyguard?
So how's a corpo rookie go from cleanin' latrines to bein' Saburo Arasaka's bodyguard?
The highest grades at the academy, service in the special forces, and Arasaka-sama's unmatched eye for talent.
You're not sayin' Saburo fell for you at first sight.
To make the right decisions with imperfect knowledge... that is how you become the world's most powerful man.
One hundred candidates standing at attention... and Arasaka-sama looked into each of our souls and chose the one who would serve him best.
Ah yes, because thieving is so much more honorable…
Least I'm not fleecin' this planet and its people in the name of profit-margins!
What is your expression... "One cannot teach an old dog new tricks."
Yes. But we need not quibble over details.
